1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:01,100
<i> Just tell me!</i>

2
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:02,600
<i> Why are you doing this?!</i>

3
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:04,633
<i>You and your friends
ruined my life</i>

4
00:00:04,633 --> 00:00:06,333
<i> because of one lie.</i>

5
00:00:06,333 --> 00:00:09,467
<i>I'll make you pay.
Every last one of you.</i>

6
00:00:11,333 --> 00:00:12,767
Please explain it all to Chloe.

7
00:00:12,767 --> 00:00:14,800
<i>Tell her that her father
isn't a murderer.</i>

8
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:16,433
<i> Love, we're going to fix this.</i>

9
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:18,100
<i>We'll get you out of here.
Promise.</i>

10
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:19,733
<i>If Anton really was
murdered here,</i>

11
00:00:19,733 --> 00:00:20,900
<i> there would be more blood.</i>

12
00:00:20,900 --> 00:00:23,067
<i>That means he was killed
somewhere else.</i>

13
00:00:23,067 --> 00:00:24,133
<i> Erica...</i>

14
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:26,233
Erica, I'm begging on my knees.

15
00:00:26,233 --> 00:00:28,267
<i> Free my husband from prison.</i>

16
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:30,600
<i> Erica, please. Help us.</i>

17
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:32,567
<i> Help my husband.</i>

18
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:36,600
Beth begged right
in front of me.

19
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:40,200
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

20
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:42,333
She wanted me
to save her family.

21
00:00:44,367 --> 00:00:46,300
To help Ryan.

22
00:00:49,167 --> 00:00:51,400
And when Ryan asked me

23
00:00:51,867 --> 00:00:53,667
if we really had a case

24
00:00:53,667 --> 00:00:54,700
[SNIFFLES]

25
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:57,100
that might clear him
of the charges tomorrow...

26
00:00:57,100 --> 00:01:00,833
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

27
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:03,133
I wanted to say yes.
But--

28
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:08,167
But suddenly, I couldn't.

29
00:01:11,333 --> 00:01:12,733
[CRYING SOFTLY]

30
00:01:12,733 --> 00:01:14,533
I couldn't do it, because...

31
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:18,533
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

32
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:21,533
I couldn't promise
that I could help him.

33
00:01:21,533 --> 00:01:22,700
What if...

34
00:01:23,733 --> 00:01:25,600
What if Edong was right?

35
00:01:28,700 --> 00:01:31,600
What if I can't save
a single person?

36
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:41,133
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

37
00:02:51,633 --> 00:02:54,800
Miss Liezel, where is Mama?

38
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,833
Did... Did something happen?

39
00:02:56,833 --> 00:02:58,667
You told me not
to use my phone.

40
00:02:58,667 --> 00:03:00,400
You said the same thing
to Joshua.

41
00:03:00,833 --> 00:03:03,300
That means something big
has happened.

42
00:03:03,733 --> 00:03:05,333
What is it?

43
00:03:05,333 --> 00:03:06,400
Uh...

44
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:09,567
Chloe, let's just wait
for your mother, okay?

45
00:03:09,567 --> 00:03:11,733
Focus on your food.
Come on now.

46
00:03:14,267 --> 00:03:15,367
[PHONE RINGING, BUZZING]

47
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:18,667
Excuse me.
I'll just answer this.

48
00:03:18,667 --> 00:03:19,967
Finish your food, okay?

49
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:28,600
[CHAIR SCRAPING]

50
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:30,900
[DRAWER RATTLING]

51
00:03:31,933 --> 00:03:33,467
What are you doing, bruh?

52
00:03:33,467 --> 00:03:34,900
She already talked to us,
remember?

53
00:03:35,767 --> 00:03:37,767
I can't wait for Mama
any longer.

54
00:03:37,767 --> 00:03:39,900
My heart's pounding
out of my chest.

55
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:44,700
Our phones are probably
just in Miss Liezel's bag.

56
00:03:44,700 --> 00:03:45,867
Do you know where it is?

57
00:03:45,867 --> 00:03:47,367
I don't.

58
00:03:47,367 --> 00:03:48,367
[HUFFS]

59
00:03:48,367 --> 00:03:55,300
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:58,733
[BOXES THUD]

61
00:03:58,733 --> 00:03:59,867
[BUBBLE WRAP CRINKLING]

62
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:16,833
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

63
00:04:20,967 --> 00:04:26,567
[MUSIC SWELLING]

64
00:04:26,567 --> 00:04:27,900
"What happened?!

65
00:04:27,933 --> 00:04:30,933
Bestie, is it true?
Your father's in prison?

66
00:04:30,933 --> 00:04:32,300
Chloe?"

67
00:04:34,433 --> 00:04:36,500
"FR? He actually killed
Anton Montenegro?"

68
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:46,033
[REPORTER]<i> Anton Montenegro,
</i> once a great TV host...

69
00:04:46,033 --> 00:04:49,733
<i>handsome, endearing,
with a kind face.</i>

70
00:04:49,733 --> 00:04:50,900
<i> Now,</i>

71
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:54,933
<i>he's all beaten up
and covered in cuts.</i>

72
00:04:54,933 --> 00:04:57,733
<i> He's soaked in his own blood.</i>

73
00:04:57,733 --> 00:04:58,867
<i> Dead.</i>

74
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:02,567
Outside a modest
car repair shop in Amurao,

75
00:05:02,933 --> 00:05:06,900
the NLEA Police
discovered Anton.

76
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:08,533
Lifeless in the early morning.

77
00:05:08,533 --> 00:05:10,467
<i>The suspect,
who is also the owner</i>

78
00:05:10,467 --> 00:05:12,933
<i>of the car repair shop,
was caught in the act</i>

79
00:05:12,933 --> 00:05:14,400
<i> His name is Ryan Mora.</i>

80
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:17,800
<i>He was still holding
the bloodied breaker bar</i>

81
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:21,367
<i>identified as
the murder weapon.</i>

82
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:25,433
<i>Ryan Mora is the husband
of Anton Montenegro's wife,</i>

83
00:05:25,433 --> 00:05:28,000
<i>Mel Montenegro, who is then
friends with the former's wife.</i>

84
00:05:28,633 --> 00:05:30,533
<i>It should be recalled
that just recently,</i>

85
00:05:30,533 --> 00:05:34,633
<i>the victim and four women,
including Mel,</i>

86
00:05:34,667 --> 00:05:37,667
<i> were involved in a scuffle</i>

87
00:05:37,667 --> 00:05:39,500
<i> at a coffee shop in Amurao.</i>

88
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:43,667
Investigators are now looking
into whether that incident

89
00:05:43,667 --> 00:05:45,767
sparked the heinous murder

90
00:05:45,767 --> 00:05:47,767
<i> of Anton Montenegro.</i>

91
00:05:47,767 --> 00:05:49,000
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS]

92
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:55,700
- [THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

93
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:03,733
[LUCAS] Do you have a copy
of the CCTV footage

94
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:05,567
from last night
until this morning?

95
00:06:05,567 --> 00:06:08,967
Did you see a mysterious man
wearing a hoodie

96
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,967
before the crime
took place?

97
00:06:10,967 --> 00:06:17,900
[THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

98
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,867
[MARCO] Edgar...

99
00:06:20,867 --> 00:06:22,867
- Inday? Right?
- That's correct.

100
00:06:22,867 --> 00:06:23,767
What time do you usually close?

101
00:06:23,767 --> 00:06:27,133
Did you see a black car
parked nearby?

102
00:06:27,133 --> 00:06:28,200
What time did you come home?

103
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:30,033
- I sent a text to...
- That's right.

104
00:06:30,033 --> 00:06:32,033
This was his message
before he left.

105
00:06:32,033 --> 00:06:33,100
Show them.

106
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:35,400
[INDAY] Before leaving work.

107
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,700
"We just finished, Yano.

108
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:40,533
Ma'am Lin's car is
already fixed.

109
00:06:40,533 --> 00:06:44,800
I just feel awkward leaving
when Boss Ryan isn't..."

110
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:51,767
[THRILLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

111
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:57,567
"OMG, Anton Montenegro
is dead!"

112
00:06:57,567 --> 00:06:59,633
"WTH! Anton passed away?"

113
00:06:59,633 --> 00:07:03,200
[MUSIC INTENSIFYING]

114
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,867
"Mel and her friends
probably murdered him!"

115
00:07:06,733 --> 00:07:07,900
[ZIPPER RASPS]

116
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:11,233
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

117
00:07:11,233 --> 00:07:12,600
Anton...

118
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:14,467
Oh my god!

119
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:15,700
[SOBBING]

120
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:16,733
I'm sorry.

121
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:18,700
You can't touch the body
just yet.

122
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:19,933
This is evidence.

123
00:07:19,933 --> 00:07:21,000
"This"?!

124
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:23,633
That's Anton!

125
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:26,767
That's my son!

126
00:07:26,767 --> 00:07:29,167
What did they do to my son?

127
00:07:29,167 --> 00:07:30,500
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

128
00:07:30,500 --> 00:07:37,233
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

129
00:07:42,933 --> 00:07:44,467
My baby...

130
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:49,233
[TELEPHONE RINGING
IN BACKGROUND]

131
00:07:50,733 --> 00:07:52,733
[RYAN SIGHS]

132
00:07:52,733 --> 00:07:55,767
Did they get a match
on the fingerprints?

133
00:07:55,767 --> 00:07:56,900
Not yet.

134
00:07:56,900 --> 00:07:58,167
Maybe tomorrow.

135
00:07:58,800 --> 00:07:59,667
[RYAN SIGHS SHARPLY]

136
00:07:59,967 --> 00:08:01,233
Hopefully they get the results
before your hearing date.

137
00:08:01,233 --> 00:08:03,800
But it's best to be prepared.

138
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:04,800
Prepared for what?

139
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:08,133
For my fingerprints to
be on the murder weapon?

140
00:08:08,133 --> 00:08:09,733
They most likely will.

141
00:08:09,733 --> 00:08:12,800
Edong probably put my
fingerprints on the breaker bar

142
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:16,100
and my blood on it
while I was unconscious.

143
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:17,533
Isn't it obvious?

144
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:21,267
About that,

145
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:25,300
I got the results from
your medico-legal exam earlier.

146
00:08:25,300 --> 00:08:27,333
Based on their findings,

147
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:30,767
there's no indication
that you lost consciousness.

148
00:08:30,767 --> 00:08:31,933
[HUFFS]

149
00:08:31,933 --> 00:08:33,000
What?

150
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:34,667
But I know what happened!

151
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:35,900
These things happen.

152
00:08:35,900 --> 00:08:38,800
But we will stand by
your statement.

153
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:41,667
I'm going to prepare
your affidavit of denial.

154
00:08:41,667 --> 00:08:43,933
You just need to state that
someone attacked you

155
00:08:43,933 --> 00:08:45,767
and you lost consciousness.

156
00:08:45,767 --> 00:08:47,300
Then when you woke up,

157
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:49,667
you found Anton's body
next to you.

158
00:08:49,667 --> 00:08:51,300
[SIGHS]

159
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:53,200
We can win this, Ryan.

160
00:08:55,667 --> 00:08:57,300
[ALICE] CCTV?

161
00:08:57,300 --> 00:08:59,367
Anton went to Amurao.

162
00:08:59,367 --> 00:09:00,967
Where did he go after?

163
00:09:00,967 --> 00:09:02,600
[SCOFFS] Here.

164
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:03,667
To see Mel.

165
00:09:03,667 --> 00:09:05,600
I told her the same thing.

166
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,200
Maybe we can check
the CCTV footage

167
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:09,267
to see if he actually came.

168
00:09:09,267 --> 00:09:12,567
Do you think he encountered
Edong when he came here?

169
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:17,667
But, uh...

170
00:09:17,667 --> 00:09:21,067
That would mean that
Edong was also here last night.

171
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:27,867
Here, I...

172
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:28,867
Look.

173
00:09:28,867 --> 00:09:32,033
There is a camera facing
outside the house

174
00:09:32,033 --> 00:09:33,367
that also captures the street.

175
00:09:39,833 --> 00:09:46,800
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

176
00:09:57,700 --> 00:09:58,800
Wait.

177
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:01,633
I think that's Anton's car.

178
00:10:01,667 --> 00:10:07,100
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

179
00:10:07,100 --> 00:10:08,400
That is his car.

180
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:12,267
[ALICE] But...

181
00:10:12,267 --> 00:10:14,367
B-But he's driving off.

182
00:10:14,367 --> 00:10:16,067
Can you zoom in
on the driver's face?

183
00:10:19,067 --> 00:10:22,033
- [BARBARA]<i> Mel! Come out here!
</i>- [BANGING GATE]

184
00:10:22,033 --> 00:10:23,200
[BANGING CONTINUES]

185
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:27,333
Are you sure about that,
Attorney?

186
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:30,167
A-Aren't they going to press
charges against me tomorrow?

187
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:33,833
I still have a chance,
right?

188
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:36,233
I want to come home
to my family.

189
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:42,133
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

190
00:10:42,133 --> 00:10:43,267
Erica!

191
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:50,333
Attorney?

192
00:10:54,067 --> 00:10:55,733
[RYAN SIGHS SOFTLY]

193
00:10:58,067 --> 00:11:05,000
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

194
00:11:12,267 --> 00:11:13,433
[DELFIN] Barbara, please.

195
00:11:13,433 --> 00:11:15,233
You'll only make things worse!

196
00:11:15,233 --> 00:11:16,767
Let's go home!

197
00:11:16,767 --> 00:11:18,967
I am not leaving
until I talk to that woman!

198
00:11:18,967 --> 00:11:20,300
Barbara.

199
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:21,967
It's okay.

200
00:11:25,067 --> 00:11:27,133
- You killed my son!
- Barbara!

201
00:11:27,133 --> 00:11:28,833
- Enough!
- You killed my son!

202
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:30,167
- Barbara!
- Enough!

203
00:11:30,167 --> 00:11:32,000
I knew this would happen!

204
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:35,300
I knew you would
ruin my son's life!

205
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,900
Attorney, you know the law.

206
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:40,833
She needs to vacate
this property immediately.

207
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:43,333
My son would still be
safe and happy

208
00:11:43,367 --> 00:11:45,300
if he never met you!

209
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:47,867
Your lying, slut
of a daughter!

210
00:11:47,867 --> 00:11:49,833
is to be blamed
for all of this!

211
00:11:51,033 --> 00:11:52,867
Your son is already dead

212
00:11:52,867 --> 00:11:55,533
and here you are still
giving him a free pass?!

213
00:11:55,533 --> 00:11:58,500
If you had held him accountable
for his actions,

214
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,367
we wouldn't have gotten here!

215
00:12:00,367 --> 00:12:02,867
It wasn't my daughter
who ruined him!

216
00:12:02,867 --> 00:12:05,733
You! You destroyed your son!

217
00:12:06,367 --> 00:12:08,167
What did you say?

218
00:12:08,167 --> 00:12:09,800
How dare you!

219
00:12:10,367 --> 00:12:14,033
I was the only one
who truly loved my son!

220
00:12:14,033 --> 00:12:15,333
Me!

221
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:19,433
It should've been your daughter
who died, not my son!

222
00:12:21,233 --> 00:12:23,333
You and your friends,

223
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:25,233
you all deserve to die!

224
00:12:25,233 --> 00:12:26,900
You're going to die!

225
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:29,000
You are all going to die!

226
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,233
Enough, Barbara.

227
00:12:30,233 --> 00:12:31,333
Let go of me!

228
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:33,233
- We need to go, Barbara!
- Don't touch me! Stop!

229
00:12:33,233 --> 00:12:35,000
- Don't touch me! Stop!
- Barbara, please.

230
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,233
[BARBARA]
You're all going to die!

231
00:12:37,233 --> 00:12:39,000
- Let's go. Let's go.
- You are going to die!

232
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,367
[DELFIN] We need to go,
Barbara.

233
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:52,533
I'm sorry
Papa's in prison, sweetie.

234
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:58,967
[VOICE BREAKING] I-I don't
want you to see me like this.

235
00:13:02,067 --> 00:13:06,400
Papa, don't say that.

236
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:09,033
I know you're innocent.

237
00:13:09,033 --> 00:13:12,233
I don't believe any of
the allegations against you.

238
00:13:14,167 --> 00:13:15,600
They're all lies.

239
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:16,900
[SNIFFLES]

240
00:13:17,433 --> 00:13:19,367
You are my Papa.

241
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:28,000
Never in a million years
would I be ashamed of you.

242
00:13:35,033 --> 00:13:36,933
[EXHALES, WHIMPERS SOFTLY]

243
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:41,100
Can you forgive me, Chloe?

244
00:13:41,900 --> 00:13:43,200
[BOTH SNIFFLE]

245
00:13:43,967 --> 00:13:46,433
This is all happening
because of me.

246
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:51,933
This is all my fault.
[SNIFFLES]

247
00:13:52,867 --> 00:13:54,300
I'm the one who
should be suffering,

248
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,533
but you're being punished
for my mistakes too.

249
00:13:58,300 --> 00:13:59,533
[EXHALES SHAKILY]

250
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:04,133
I love you, Ma.

251
00:14:04,933 --> 00:14:06,200
[SOBS]

252
00:14:07,633 --> 00:14:12,033
What happened in the past
doesn't matter anymore.

253
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:15,967
All I want...

254
00:14:19,067 --> 00:14:21,133
...is for all of us
to be together again.

255
00:14:23,067 --> 00:14:25,067
For us to be happy.

256
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:32,133
Can we hit reset...

257
00:14:33,267 --> 00:14:35,600
...and go back to
how things were before?

258
00:14:38,033 --> 00:14:39,967
Can we do that?

259
00:14:42,633 --> 00:14:45,567
[CRYING]

260
00:14:47,967 --> 00:14:54,933
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

261
00:15:09,667 --> 00:15:16,633
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

262
00:15:31,567 --> 00:15:38,533
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

263
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:42,600
[RYAN ON VIDEO]
<i> What do you have there, Gar?</i>

264
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,233
<i> Is that for Inday?</i>

265
00:15:44,233 --> 00:15:46,433
<i>Hey, Inday!
Keep a close eye on him!</i>

266
00:15:46,433 --> 00:15:48,367
<i>- Hey, Ryan!
- What?</i>

267
00:15:50,667 --> 00:15:51,567
<i> Don't believe--</i>

268
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:01,133
[PHONE BUZZING]

269
00:16:03,433 --> 00:16:04,733
[MARCO] So, have you seen it?

270
00:16:05,533 --> 00:16:08,767
No wonder I couldn't
reach Edgar before.

271
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,800
His phone was busted.

272
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:14,100
<i>Good thing his girlfriend
sent me that video.</i>

273
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:17,100
Do you think Ryan
could have smiled like that

274
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:18,767
if he had really killed
Anton?

275
00:16:20,300 --> 00:16:21,600
Who are you trying to fool?

276
00:16:23,300 --> 00:16:25,267
<i> I could say that</i>

277
00:16:25,267 --> 00:16:28,600
you just made a video to
create an alibi for the crime.

278
00:16:30,033 --> 00:16:31,467
That's what the prosecutor
would say

279
00:16:31,467 --> 00:16:33,533
if I present the video
she forwarded to you.

280
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:39,600
Thank you, Marco,
but this won't help our case.

281
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:42,633
[MARCO]<i> Then let's find
</i> another way to win.

282
00:16:42,667 --> 00:16:45,433
I know you can come up
with something.

283
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:48,500
[ANNETTE]<i> You never
</i> should've been born!

284
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:50,500
<i> You never should've lived!</i>

285
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:52,300
<i> You should die!</i>

286
00:16:56,433 --> 00:16:57,467
Erica?

287
00:16:58,467 --> 00:16:59,800
[EDONG] You're useless.

288
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:02,267
<i> You're no savior.</i>

289
00:17:02,267 --> 00:17:06,500
<i>You know what you are?
You're a big phony, Attorney.</i>

290
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,767
<i> A big, useless phony.</i>

291
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:14,433
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

292
00:17:14,433 --> 00:17:15,467
Where are you?

293
00:17:16,467 --> 00:17:17,567
<i> I'm coming.</i>

294
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:23,100
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

295
00:17:23,100 --> 00:17:29,833
- [HIGH-PITCHED RINGING]
- [HEART POUNDING]

296
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:34,067
[MARCO] Why weren't you
answering my calls?

297
00:17:37,167 --> 00:17:38,200
[VOICE ECHOING]
I thought you...

298
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,333
[RINGING SWELLS, ENDS]

299
00:17:39,333 --> 00:17:41,600
Don't do this, Erica.

300
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:43,467
Edong's still out there.

301
00:17:43,467 --> 00:17:45,167
He just killed Anton, remember?

302
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:49,133
I've made a life for myself!

303
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:54,567
I've proven myself to everyone.

304
00:17:54,567 --> 00:17:57,167
Who I am, what I can do.

305
00:17:58,700 --> 00:18:01,300
It doesn't matter
why I was born

306
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:03,200
because I had
no control over that!

307
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:11,300
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

308
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:14,367
But I can't shake it off
my mind.

309
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:20,700
And to be honest,

310
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:25,133
I am not okay.

311
00:18:26,267 --> 00:18:28,733
[SOBBING]

312
00:18:29,767 --> 00:18:30,767
[SNIFFLES]

313
00:18:30,767 --> 00:18:35,233
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

314
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:39,567
[ERICA] I hear it
over and over again.

315
00:18:39,567 --> 00:18:41,133
Up here.

316
00:18:42,233 --> 00:18:47,200
I keep hearing my mom say
I never should've been born.

317
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:50,600
So I wouldn't end up
like my rapist father

318
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:52,833
who's nothing but
a stain on this world!

319
00:18:52,833 --> 00:18:54,700
Like some
worthless piece of dirt!

320
00:18:57,800 --> 00:19:00,267
Why won't she leave me alone?!

321
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:09,200
Erica.

322
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:12,400
That's not true.

323
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:15,533
That voice does not
dictate who you are.

324
00:19:17,533 --> 00:19:18,600
It's your courage,

325
00:19:20,567 --> 00:19:21,900
your decisions,

326
00:19:21,900 --> 00:19:23,367
the things you're fighting for.

327
00:19:24,733 --> 00:19:28,433
That's what you are.

328
00:19:31,567 --> 00:19:33,267
That's what you should
believe in.

329
00:19:38,300 --> 00:19:40,933
Beth was begging me.

330
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:43,633
<i> Erica, I beg you...</i>

331
00:19:43,633 --> 00:19:45,800
[CRYING]

332
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:48,800
<i>Erica, please bring
my husband home!</i>

333
00:19:50,667 --> 00:19:51,767
[SOBBING]

334
00:19:51,767 --> 00:19:54,567
<i> Please help us, Erica.</i>

335
00:19:56,333 --> 00:19:59,267
And Ryan asked me earlier if...

336
00:19:59,267 --> 00:20:01,667
if we really had a chance
to win this.

337
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:04,433
<i>Are you sure about that,
Attorney?</i>

338
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:07,500
<i>Aren't they going to press
charges against me tomorrow?</i>

339
00:20:09,367 --> 00:20:10,967
<i> I still have a chance, right?</i>

340
00:20:11,767 --> 00:20:13,500
<i>I want to come home
to my family.</i>

341
00:20:14,933 --> 00:20:17,300
[ERICA] I wanted to say yes,
but...

342
00:20:20,367 --> 00:20:22,267
I couldn't.

343
00:20:25,367 --> 00:20:26,867
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

344
00:20:26,867 --> 00:20:29,433
I couldn't because...

345
00:20:32,533 --> 00:20:36,767
I wasn't sure if
I could help him because...

346
00:20:37,900 --> 00:20:39,800
maybe Edong is right.

347
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:45,933
I won't be able to save anyone.

348
00:20:47,633 --> 00:20:48,667
[SNIFFLES]

349
00:20:48,667 --> 00:20:51,933
I saw how hard it was
for Mel, Alice, and Beth

350
00:20:52,700 --> 00:20:56,700
to admit their mistakes.

351
00:20:58,667 --> 00:20:59,633
[SNIFFLES]

352
00:21:01,567 --> 00:21:03,933
I feel like
I'm the bad guy.

353
00:21:07,033 --> 00:21:09,500
But I told myself that...

354
00:21:10,600 --> 00:21:12,733
this is what needs to be done.

355
00:21:15,833 --> 00:21:19,733
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

356
00:21:19,733 --> 00:21:21,433
[GUN COCKS, CLICKS]

357
00:21:21,433 --> 00:21:23,533
[CHUCKLES]

358
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:28,533
Are you going to
help me finish the job?

359
00:21:29,667 --> 00:21:31,867
They need to pay.

360
00:21:33,933 --> 00:21:35,700
Alice...

361
00:21:36,933 --> 00:21:39,000
...and Attorney Erica
need to pay.

362
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:43,567
I thought I was
the right person for this.

363
00:21:46,533 --> 00:21:48,700
But I'm starting to think
I was wrong.

364
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:54,733
Maybe I should stop
before more people get hurt.

365
00:21:57,433 --> 00:21:59,467
Maybe it's time for me
to give up already.

366
00:21:59,467 --> 00:22:05,033
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

367
00:22:05,033 --> 00:22:08,600
[EDONG] I gave
Attorney Erica my word...

368
00:22:11,367 --> 00:22:12,400
[IMITATES GUNSHOT]

369
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:19,333
[LAUGHING]

370
00:22:29,100 --> 00:22:33,433
[LAUGHING CONTINUES]

371
00:22:35,967 --> 00:22:37,667
<i>Reputation alone
cannot acquit a man.</i>

372
00:22:37,667 --> 00:22:39,000
Still, I submit the certificate

373
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:40,967
<i>that reflects the life
my client has lived.</i>

374
00:22:40,967 --> 00:22:42,767
<i>This certificate
looks impressive,</i>

375
00:22:42,767 --> 00:22:44,933
<i>but in my office,
this is just a piece of paper</i>

376
00:22:44,933 --> 00:22:48,733
that can easily go up in flames
once the truth comes to light.

377
00:22:48,767 --> 00:22:51,800
<i>I have no choice but to
press charges against Mr. Mora!</i>

378
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:53,100
[SOBS]

379
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:55,700
<i>We asked you all to come here
today to give a statement</i>

380
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:57,767
<i>on an incident
that happened 14 years ago.</i>

381
00:22:57,767 --> 00:23:01,667
<i> I will rectify  their mistake.</i>

382
00:23:01,667 --> 00:23:03,500
<i> That is my mission.</i>
